  "bio_raw": "He has over three years of experience in academia and research, specializing in operations research, supply chain optimization, and logistics management. Currently serving as a Lecturer in Supply Chain Management at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh. He holds a Master of Science in Industrial Engineering from Texas State University, where his research focused on stochastic vehicle routing problems for nonprofit organizations. His expertise spans mathematical modeling, optimization algorithms, and simulation techniques. He has published research on pandemic management strategies and presented award-winning work at international conferences. His research interests include last-mile delivery optimization, decision analytics under uncertainty, and supply chain disruptions, demonstrating a strong commitment to developing practical solutions for complex logistics challenges.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Linear Programming, Stochastic Programming, Supply Chain Optimization, Vehicle Routing Problem."
  ],
